 simulations suggest that\ndeep [C II] observation with ALMA can trace the distribution of neutral gas\nextending over $\\sim 20$ physical kpc. We also find that the luminosity ratio\n$L_{\\rm [O\\,III]}/L_{\\rm [C\\,II]}$ decreases with bolometric luminosity due to\nmetal enrichment. Our simulations show that the combination of multi-wavelength\nobservations by ALMA and JWST will be able to reveal the multi-phase ISM\nstructure and the transition from starbursting to outflowing phases of high-z\ngalaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 5 Aug 2019 01:33:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-06-10"}
